<p dir="auto">If you're using Modular CSS such as, CSS Modules, <code>postcss-loader</code> or <code>vanilla-extract</code> to name a few, you'll probably
notice that custom media queries are not being resolved. This happens because each file is processed separately so
unless you import the custom media query definitions in each file, they won't be resolved.</p>
<p dir="auto">To overcome this, we recommend using the <a href="https://github.com/csstools/postcss-plugins/tree/main/plugins/postcss-global-data#readme">PostCSS Global Data</a>
plugin which allows you to pass a list of files that will be globally available. The plugin won't inject any extra code
in the output but will provide the context needed to resolve custom media queries.</p>
<p dir="auto">For it to run it needs to be placed before the <a href="https://github.com/csstools/postcss-plugins/tree/main/plugins/postcss-custom-media">PostCSS Custom Media</a> plugin.</p>
